{
  "stem": "12255.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I call it rough because what used to happen was, that coming and going at your cheder, which was, from my home-- we didn't live in a very Jewish area-- it was about a mile and a half, two miles.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the way back, we would pass through an area which was a little bit rough.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And very often, we were chased by other youngsters, and unpleasant names called after us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And usually one of our older brothers would accompany us, in case we were attacked, or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a lot of that kind of thing amongst the-- the youngsters, who very likely learned it from their parents.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, there were no Jewish schools.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jewish school was the cheder, which we attended every afternoon for some three hours.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and then I went on to the yeshiva, which was under the leadership of Rabbi [INAUDIBLE], who later became the chief rabbi of Israel.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and I continued my studies there at the yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I was qualified by the-- the rabbi-- the Rabbi [INAUDIBLE], the chief rabbi, and served as a-- with the title of Reverend at first, in a little place in North Wales called Bangor, a very pretty place, very pretty indeed, and then in a small industrial town-- well, not so small by South African standards-- called Bolton, near Manchester.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was from about 1937, and first in-- in Bangor for a couple of years, and then in Bolton, until I went-- went into the army.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, frankly, I don't think it affected very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Despite what I said about the youngsters persecuting us, we found very little anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, my parents, as I said, lived in a completely non-Jewish area.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There weren't many Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
